<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900703-0127</DOCNO><DOCID>900703-0127.</DOCID><HL>   REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:   School Reform</HL><DATE>07/03/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10</SO><LP>   The Los Angeles school board has relented to publicpressure and voted 6-1 to expel kids who bring guns to highschools or junior highs. Knives and BB-guns are still not anautomatic cause for dismissal in the 610,000-studentdistrict. Board member Rita Walters, from a central-city areaworst affected by campus violence, was a holdout to the end,saying that firearm-toters should instead be taught to &quot;writeand read and compute . . . so they have a sense ofbelonging.&quot; Her constituents seem to have a better sense ofwhere those characters belong and don't belong.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>